        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Vineland, or 9 miles northeast of Thomasville. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Thomaston, Wayne, Surginer, Shawnee, Dixons Mill, Magnolia, Vineland,
Clayhill, and Nicholsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
